sentence: Knut Nystedt (3 September 1915 – 8 December 2014) was a Norwegian orchestral and choral composer.
Knut Nystedt (3 September 1915 – 8 December 2014) was a Norwegian orchestral and choral composer.
Nystedt was born in Kristiania (now Oslo), Norway, and grew up in a Christian home where hymns and classical music were an important part of everyday life.
